title: A1466 I/O BOARD
message:
Hi!

I have about 3 i/o boards that the the thing marked in the circle got burned. that happens when piece o metal gets inside the magnetized charger and burn it.

What is that and how can I replaced? how can I fix it? thanks

title: A1466 I/O BOARD
message:
uCalmp2401T, ESD protection diode.
Usually killed by fake chargers.
Original charger only serves 3V (Magsafe 2) on output (low current), before handshake protocol is done.
